Privacy Policy

DATA PROTECTION DECLARATION

   With this Privacy Policy we would like to inform you about how we
   process personal data and what information is collected when you use
   our services.

   We are aware of the importance of the processing of personal data for
   the user and accordingly comply with all relevant legal requirements.
   The protection of your privacy is of utmost importance to us. Please
   read this entire document to fully understand our actions.

Contact and data protection officer

   Opinary GmbH
   Managing Director Cornelius Frey
   Engeldamm 62-64
   10179 Berlin
   Germany

   privacy@opinary.com

   We have appointed a Privacy Officer to help us ensure and enforce our
   privacy policy:

   Eprivacy GmbH represented by Prof. Dr. med. Christoph Bauer
   Große Bleiche 21
   20354 Hamburg
   +49 40 609451 810
   info@eprivacy.com

Glossary

   In this privacy policy, the following terms may appear, which are
   defined in more detail below.
   advertisers An entity that buys advertising space or marketing services
   from Opinary GmbH.
   computer Any device that provides access to digital content. Includes:
   desktop computers, laptops, tablets, cell phones or other connected
   devices.
   editor (dashboard) Our CMS, with which opinary GmbH can design polls
   and configure them.
   Personal data (PII) All information about personal and factual
   circumstances of a particular or identifiable person. This includes
   information and details such as your name, address or alternative
   postal address, telephone number or your e-mail address.
   Publisher An entity that has permission and access to Opinary GmbH
   Service and uses it in accordance with our terms.
   service Access and use of our polls, tools and Dashboard
   Tool / Poll The digital polls that run on the site of a publisher
   through the embed codes provided by us.
   User Any end user using our services.

How we receive information

   We receive information (including possibly personal information) from
   different sources.
     * If you voluntarily provide us your personal details within our
       Services (for example by registering, using your Publisher
       Dashboard access or by subscribing to our newsletter)
     * If you visit the opinary.com homepage or using our dashboard
     * From third party websites and services where our tools are embedded

Uses

   Opinary GmbH offers a service that allows users to vote on editorial as
   well as sponsored polls. In this context, our service automatically
   stores a cookie on the user’s computer, which allows us to summarize
   voting results in a statistically meaningful way and to optimize our
   service and the information presented in the interests of the user.
   This cookie is based on a randomized online identifier.

   The additional data collected will include the category of the content
   of the website visited, the type of Opinary Tools used, language of the
   content, browser, operating system, device type, location information,
   and whether you are voting or otherwise clicking or interacting with
   any content. This information is combined with the identifier to form a
   user profile. The user profile does not contain names, postal
   addresses, telephone numbers, e-mail addresses or similar personal
   data.

   The data collected will be used, among other things, for the following
   purposes:
     * To generate relevant aggregates (without any reference to personal
       information) from our online polls, display them and make them
       available to our partners
     * To recommend products, services or other relevant polls
     * Improvement of our services
     * Protection against abuse
     * statistics

   If you do not want your data to be used this way, you can contradict
   via our Opt Out function:
   https://compass.pressekompass.net/static/optout.html

   —

   In addition, personal data will be collected by us only and only to the
   extent and for the purpose for which you provide us with the data, eg.
   in the context of a registration. Examples include marketing
   communications, any information requests from your side, or information
   we collect from you to enter into a business relationship.

   —

   Statistical information helps to understand trends and customer needs
   so that they can be utilised in new products and services as well as
   improving existing products and services. Opinary GmbH does not
   knowingly collect or store any information that enables us to determine
   the true identity of users, and we ensure that this will be impossible
   in the future, through regular auditing and encryption mechanisms.

Legal basis of data processing

   Our legal basis for the collection and use of the personal data
   described in this Privacy Policy depends on the personal data concerned
   and the specific context in which we collect it.

   Basically, the data processing takes place on the following legal
   bases:
     * With regard to data that you specify in forms, etc., with your
       consent, Art. 6 para. 1 lit. a) GDPR
     * in relation to the services you use to carry out a contract with
       you, Art. 6 (1) lit. b) GDPR
     * for the rest, in particular for statistical data and online
       identifiers, on the basis of legitimate interests, Art. 6 para. 1
       lit. f) GDPR

   When we collect and use your personal information for legitimate
   interests (or that of a third party), that interest is usually in the
   provision of our services and our commercial interests. For example,
   answering your inquiries, improving our tools and services, marketing
   or preventing illegal activity. We may have other legitimate interests
   and, if appropriate, we will make it clear to you at the relevant time
   within the tool which legitimate interests they are.

Data security measurements

   We have taken extensive technical and organizational measures to
   safeguard your information against possible risks, such as unauthorized
   access, unauthorized modification or dissemination, loss, destruction
   or misuse. You can contact us at privacy@opinary.com if you want to
   have a more granular outline of our Technical Security Measurements and
   Strategy.

   Actions include, but are not limited to, the safekeeping of your data
   in secure, firewall-protected, and through other means secured servers
   running at certified facilities. Strict internal guidelines determine
   who has access to and what volume of data within Opinary GmbH. In
   addition, it ensures that only Opinary GmbH employees have access to
   your personal information and we are constantly working to improve our
   security standards when appropriate new technologies become available.

   In order to protect your personal data from unauthorized third-party
   access during transmission, we secure the data transmissions using SSL
   encryption if necessary. It is a standardized encryption method for
   online services, especially for the Web.

   While we perform the steps outlined above to ensure that your data is
   safe in our system, data transmission over the Internet can not be
   guaranteed to be 100% secure. For that reason, we cannot guarantee the
   security of the information you provide to us. You do this at your own
   risk.

Your rights

     * You have the right to request information as to whether and which
       personal data we process through you. You also have the right to
       request the correction of your personal data or its completion.
     * In certain circumstances, you have the right to request that your
       personal information be deleted.
     * In certain circumstances, you have the right to request that the
       processing of your personal data be restricted.
     * You may withdraw your consent to the processing and use of your
       data in whole or in part at any time with future effect.
     * You have the right to receive your personal information in a
       standard, structured and machine-readable format.
     * If you have any questions, comments or complaints or requests for
       information in connection with our privacy policy and the
       processing of your personal data, you can contact our data
       protection officer in writing.
     * You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the relevant
       regulatory authority if you believe that the processing of your
       personal data violates the law.

   You can contact us for questions about the above points at
   privacy@opinary.com.

   We respond to any requests we receive from individuals wishing to
   exercise their privacy rights in accordance with applicable privacy
   laws.

Requirement or obligation to provide data

   Unless specifically stated in the survey/poll, the provision of data is
   not required or mandatory.

Data transmission to third countries

   Data may be transferred to third countries outside the European Union.
   This is done on the basis of legally provided contractual arrangements,
   which should ensure an adequate protection of your data.

   All our communications are protected by the standard contractual
   clauses and data processing contracts of the European Commission, as
   provided for in the European Data Protection Act. You can see these
   documents on request.

Cookies

   Cookies are small files that your browser places on your device in a
   designated directory. These cookies can be used to determine, for
   example, whether you have visited a website before. Most browsers
   accept cookies automatically. However, you can set your browser so that
   no cookies are stored or an explicit consent is required before saving
   a cookie. In addition, you can delete previously set cookies at any
   time.

   For more information about blocking cookies in your particular web
   browser, see allaboutcookies.org .

   Please note that disabling cookies may result in restrictions on the
   use of our website and services.

   Depending on the service, we store the following cookies under the
   domains compass.pressekompass.net and * .opinary.com.

   Opinary Opt Out Cookie (“_op_optout”)

   This cookie informs the Opinary service that a user opted out and thus
   no further data is processed or stored.

   Opinary User Cookie (“u”, “fpd”)

   This cookie contains a randomized identifier, by means of which Opinary
   GmbH can combine the surfing behavior of a user into a user profile.

   Opinary Vote (“_opinary_vote”)

   This cookie indicates whether a user has already voted on a specific
   poll.

   Opinary Editor Authentication (“auth”)

   This cookie is set only for users of our Dashboard and allows the user
   to identify themselves as authenticated. Without this cookie, a user of
   the Dashboard would have to log in before use or each step.

   Google cookies (ie “_ga”, “_gat UA”, “__utma”, “__utmz”)

   These cookies are set by our service provider Google Analytics and give
   the Opinary GmbH the opportunity to analyze the surfing behavior of
   users. Google’s privacy policy can be found here:
   www.google.com/privacy.html

Usage-related advertising

   The advertising displayed in the services of the Opinary GmbH is
   partially optimized for you by the anonymous collection and processing
   of your usage behavior, so that you get advertisement tailored to your
   interests. For this purpose, a cookie is stored on your computer.
   Behavioral targeting and retargeting are operated by third parties who
   also advertise websites of other providers. These third-party companies
   then create their own usage profiles by means of cookies and use their
   respective targeting systems to select the collected data for the
   purpose of user-friendly advertising.

   In addition to the usual methods of opting-out and blocking cookies via
   the browser, you also have the option of deactivating cookies with
   regard to usage-based advertising: the preference manager of the BVDW,
     www.meine-cookies.org/cookies_verwalten/praeferenzmanager-beta.html ,
   as well as the preference management of YourOnlineChoices,
   www.youronlinechoices.com/de/praferenzmanagement/

Web analytics

   Like almost every website operator, we use tracking software analysis
   tools to determine the frequency and number of users on our website.

   In order to optimize this website and our services, we use Google
   Analytics, a web analytics service provided by Google Inc. (“Google”).
   Google Analytics uses cookies, text files that are stored on your
   computer and enable an analysis of your use of the website. The
   information generated by the cookie about your use of this website
   (including your IP address) will be transmitted to a Google server in
   the USA and stored there. However, if you enable IP anonymization on
   this website, your Google IP address will be truncated beforehand
   within Member States of the European Union or in other signatory states
   to the EEA Agreement. Only in exceptional cases is the full IP address
   transferred to a Google server in the USA and truncated there. On
   behalf of the operator of this website, Google will use this
   information to evaluate your use of the website, to compile reports on
   website activity for the website operator and to provide further
   services associated with the use of the website and the Internet to the
   website operator.

   The IP address transmitted by your browser within the scope of Google
   Analytics will not be merged with other Google data. You can prevent
   the storage of cookies by setting your browser software accordingly;
   however, we would like to point out that in this case you may not be
   able to use all the functions of this website and our tools and
   services to their full extent. You can also prevent Google from
   collecting the data generated by the cookie and relating to your use of
   the website (including your IP address) and from processing this data
   by Google by downloading and installing the browser plug-in available
   under the following link: tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout?hl=en.

   For more information, please visit
   tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout?hl=en or
   www.google.com/intl/de/analytics/privacyoverview.html (general
   information about Google Analytics and data protection). We would like
   to point out that on this website Google Analytics has been extended by
   the code “gat._anonymizeIp();” in order to guarantee an anonymous
   capture of IP addresses (so-called IP masking).

   We use Google AdWords Remarketing to advertise Opinary across the
   Internet. AdWords remarketing will display relevant ads tailored to you
   based on what parts of the Opinary website you have viewed by placing a
   cookie on your machine. This cookie does not in anyway identify you or
   give access to your computer. The cookie is used to say “This person
   visited this page, so show them ads relating to that page.” Google
   AdWords Remarketing allows us to tailor our marketing to better suit
   your needs and only display ads that are relevant to you.

   If you do not wish to participate in our Google AdWords Remarketing,
   you can opt out by visiting Google’s Ads Preferences Manager

   You can also opt out of any third-party vendor’s use of cookies by
   visiting www.networkadvertising.org/choices/

Logfiles

   Every time you access our Internet pages, usage data is transmitted
   through the respective Internet browser and stored in log files, the
   so-called server log files. The records stored in this case contain the
   following data:
     * Domain from which the user accesses the website
     * Date and time of retrieval
     * IP address of the accessing computer
     * Website (s) that the user visits as part of the offer
     * Transmitted amount of data, browser type and version
     * Operating system used Name of the Internet service provider
     * Message if the retrieval was successful

   These logfile records are evaluated anonymously to improve the offering
   and make it more user-friendly, to find and fix bugs, and to control
   server load.

Data sources

   Unless otherwise stated, we will receive the information from you
   (including the equipment you use).

Storage time

   We store your data,
     * if you have consented to the processing at most until you revoke
       your consent
     * if we need the data to execute a contract, at most as long as the
       contractual relationship with you or statutory retention periods
       are in effect,
     * if we use the data on the basis of a legitimate interest, at most
       as long as your interest in deletion or anonymization does not
       prevail. All personally identifiable information (PII) information
       that we collect from you will be processed after a period of one
       year in such a way that the personal connection to an original
       person can no longer be established.

Links to the websites of third parties

   Opinary may refer to the website of third parties that provide useful
   information / services. All information that the user makes available
   on the linked pages is passed on directly to these third-party
   providers and is subject to the privacy policy of the respective
   provider. Opinary is not responsible for the content or privacy
   practices of websites it links to. Links from Opinary’s Service to
   third parties or other websites are provided for the convenience of the
   user. You should consult the privacy policies of each website before
   providing them with personal information.

Social networks

Facebook

   Facebook is operated by Facebook Inc. of 1601 S. California Ave, Palo
   Alto, CA 94304, USA and is available at www.facebook.de. These
   individual social plugins are identified by one of the Facebook logos
   or with the addition “Facebook Social Plugin”. A list of the appearance
   and functions of each plugin can be found here: developers.
   facebook.com/docs/plugins. When you access a page of our website that
   contains such a social plugin, the browser you are using will establish
   a direct connection to Facebook’s servers. The content of the social
   plugin is sent directly from Facebook to your browser and integrated
   into the website by your browser. We have no control over the amount of
   data that Facebook collects using the social plugins, and therefore we
   would like to inform you about this to the best of our knowledge: Due
   to the inclusion of the social plugins, Facebook will be informed that
   you have visited the corresponding page of our website, even if you are
   not registered as a Facebook user or not logged in to Facebook. This
   information is sent from your browser to a Facebook server in the
   United States together with your IP address and saved there. According
   to the information provided by Facebook, only an anonymous IP address
   of non-registered users in Germany is stored. If you are logged in to
   Facebook, Facebook can make a connection between your Facebook account
   and visiting our website. Facebook receives information about your
   visit to our website regardless of whether you interact with the social
   plugins or not.

   If you interact with the social plugins, for example by clicking on the
   “Like” button or by submitting a comment, the corresponding information
   is sent directly from your browser to Facebook and stored there. The
   information is also published on Facebook and displayed to your
   Facebook friends. For the purpose and scope of data collection and
   further processing and use of the data by Facebook, as well as your
   rights and options for privacy protection, please refer to Facebook’s
   Privacy Policy, which is available at www.facebook.com/about/privacy.
   If you are a registered user of Facebook and do not want Facebook to
   collect information about you through our website and link it to your
   Facebook-membership data, you must log out of Facebook before visiting
   our website. It is also possible to block the social plugins with
   add-ons for your browser, such as Facebook Blocker,
   webgraph.com/resources/facebookblocker.

Twitter

   This website uses the buttons of the Twitter service provided by
   Twitter Inc., 1355 Market St, Suite 900, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA.
   These plugins are recognizable by terms such as “Twitter” or “Tweet” or
   the Twitter logo. They allow you to share a post or a page of this
   website on Twitter. When a user accesses a web page that contains such
   a button, his browser establishes a direct connection to Twitter’s
   servers. The content of the Twitter button is sent directly to the
   user’s browser by Twitter. We have no influence on the amount of data
   that Twitter collects with the help of this plugin and can therefore
   only inform the user according to our knowledge: Afterwards, log data
   such as the IP address of the user, the previously accessed website,
   etc. are transmitted. For more information, please see the Twitter
   Privacy Policy at twitter.com/privacy.

